\f1\b When you run:
\f0\b0 \
\
```bash\
cd ~/nexus-enterprise\
./start-dev.sh\
```\
this is what happens step by step:\
\

\f1\b ### 1. Hard reset of ports and Node dev processes
\f0\b0 \
\
```bash path="/Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/start-dev.sh" start=8 end=18\
echo "=== HARD RESET: killing dev processes and restarting Nexus dev (Cloud SQL nexusdev-v2) ==="\
\
echo "\uc0\u8594  Killing anything on ports 3000, 8000, 5432, 6380\'85"\
for PORT in 3000 8000 5432 6380; do\
  if lsof -iTCP:$PORT -sTCP:LISTEN >/dev/null 2>&1; then\
    echo "  - Port $PORT in use, killing processes..."\
    lsof -iTCP:$PORT -sTCP:LISTEN -t | xargs kill -9 || true\
  else\
    echo "  - Port $PORT is free."\
  fi\
done\
```\
- For each of ports **3000, 8000, 5432, 6380**:\
  - If something is listening on that port, it prints a message and sends `kill -9` to all PIDs on that port (force kill).\
  - If nothing is there, it says the port is free.\
- Then it kills common Node dev processes by pattern:\
\
```bash path="/Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/start-dev.sh" start=20 end=25\
echo "\uc0\u8594  Killing common Node dev processes (node/next/nodemon/ts-node-dev)\'85"\
pkill -f "next dev" 2>/dev/null || true\
pkill -f "nodemon" 2>/dev/null || true\
pkill -f "ts-node-dev" 2>/dev/null || true\
pkill -f "node .*apps/api" 2>/dev/null || true\
pkill -f "node .*apps/web" 2>/dev/null || true\
```\
- This ensures no stale Next/Nodemon/ts-node-dev or app-specific Node processes are left running.\
\

\f1\b ### 2. Switch into the repo and stop Docker infra
\f0\b0 \
\
```bash path="/Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/start-dev.sh" start=27 end=35\
echo "\uc0\u8594  Changing to repo: $REPO_DIR"\
cd "$REPO_DIR"\
\
echo "\uc0\u8594  Stopping Docker infra (if running)\'85"\
if [ -f "$COMPOSE_FILE" ]; then\
  docker compose -f "$COMPOSE_FILE" down || true\
else\
  echo "  \uc0\u9888 \u65039  Compose file not found at $COMPOSE_FILE"\
fi\
```\
- `REPO_DIR` is `$HOME/nexus-enterprise`.\
- It `cd`s there.\
- If `infra/docker/docker-compose.yml` exists, it runs:\
\
```bash\
  docker compose -f infra/docker/docker-compose.yml down\
```\
  to stop Postgres/Redis containers (if they\'92re running).  \
  If Docker isn\'92t running, you\'92ll see a warning, but the script continues.\
\

\f1\b ### 3. Check that `DEV_DB_PASSWORD` is set
\f0\b0 \
\
```bash path="/Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/start-dev.sh" start=37 end=41\
echo "\uc0\u8594  Delegating dev startup to scripts/dev-start.sh (Cloud SQL on 5434)\'85"\
if [[ -z "$\{DEV_DB_PASSWORD:-\}" ]]; then\
  echo "  \uc0\u9888 \u65039  DEV_DB_PASSWORD is not set. Export it before running start-dev.sh (e.g. export DEV_DB_PASSWORD='<your_dev_db_password>')." >&2\
  exit 1\
fi\
```\
- If `DEV_DB_PASSWORD` is **not** set in your environment:\
  - It prints a warning and **exits** (no dev stack is started).\
- If it **is** set:\
  - It proceeds to the next step.\
\

\f1\b ### 4. Delegate to `scripts/dev-start.sh`\

\f0\b0 \
```bash path="/Users/pg/nexus-enterprise/start-dev.sh" start=43 end=45\
bash "$REPO_DIR/scripts/dev-start.sh"\
\
echo "=== Dev environment started via scripts/dev-start.sh (API :8000, Web :3000, DB nexusdev-v2 on :5434) ==="\
```\
At this point, `scripts/dev-start.sh` does the rest:\
\
- Verifies:\
  - `cloud-sql-proxy` is on `PATH`.\
  - `npm` is on `PATH`.\
  - (If no credential file is set) `gcloud` project is `nexus-enterprise-480610` (otherwise it exits with an error and a fix).\
- Ensures `apps/web/.env.local` points to `http://localhost:8000`.\
- Starts (or reuses) **Cloud SQL Auth Proxy** to `nexusdev-v2` on `127.0.0.1:5434` using your `gcloud` Application Default Credentials.\
- Exports `DATABASE_URL` pointing at `postgres://postgres:$\{DEV_DB_PASSWORD\}@127.0.0.1:5434/nexus_db`.\
- Starts, in the background:\
  - API dev server (Nest, `npm run dev` in `apps/api`) listening on `http://localhost:8000`.\
  - API worker (`npm run worker:dev` in `apps/api`).\
  - Web dev server (`npm run dev` in `apps/web`) listening on `http://localhost:3000`.\
\
So, **after `./start-dev.sh` completes successfully**, you should have:\
\
- Cloud SQL proxy \uc0\u8594  `nexusdev-v2` on `127.0.0.1:5434`.\
- API \uc0\u8594  `http://localhost:8000`.\
- Web \uc0\u8594  `http://localhost:3000`.\
- Worker running for background jobs.\
\
If you want, next we can run `./start-dev.sh` once more and cross-check with `lsof` + the logs to confirm everything lines up with that description in your current session.}